Speaker: Gina Häußge Track:PyConDE OctoPrint is an open source web interface for 3D printers and deployed world wide on a large variety of devices. In this talk I explain some of the challenges in developing and maintaining such a piece of end user facing software in Python. Recorded at the PyConDE & PyData Berlin 2019 conference. https://pycon.de More details at the conference page: https://de.pycon.org/program/JQAUEC Twitter: https://twitter.com/pydataberlin Twitter: https://twitter.com/pyconde
